### Environment Variables Example
## This file demonstrates using environment variables from
## http-client.env.json (public) and http-client.private.env.json (private).
##
## The active environment is set by "activeEnv" in http-client.env.json.
## Change it to switch between development, staging, production.
##
## Available environments: development, staging, production

### GET request using environment base_url
GET {{base_url}}/get
Accept: application/json

### GET with API key from environment
GET {{api_url}}/headers
X-Api-Key: {{api_key}}
Accept: application/json

### POST with auth token from environment
POST {{api_url}}/post
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Hello from {{base_url}}"
}

### Mix file variables with environment variables
@endpoint = /anything

GET {{base_url}}{{endpoint}}
X-Custom-Value: my-value
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### Capture response and combine with env vars
POST {{api_url}}/post
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "environment": "development",
  "api_key": "{{api_key}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("request_url", response.body.url);
%}

###

### Use captured variable from previous request
GET {{base_url}}/get?previous_url={{request_url}}
Accept: application/json
